My Project Service is depends on User Service, What if User service goes down then if product service is looking for user service with the feign client then user service donot send any reponse back if it is down then we will get the 500 internal server error

This is called:Cascading Failure
Circuit Breaker States has 3 states :
1. CLOSED (Normal)
2. OPEN (Failure Detected)
3. HALF OPEN (Testing Phase)

closed: if 10 calls from product to user then only 1 is failure that is ok
open: if 10 calls from product to user then 6 were the failures then circuit breaker opens then requests are blocked immediately
half open: if success Circuit closes again, if failure Circuit opens again

So the flow is same , controller calls the service and inside service interface we have a method getProjectForUser and in the impl we aer impl and saying that protect this method with circuit breaker and this method getProjectForUser calls by the circuit breaker if not reaches then the fallbackMethod returs it

inside yml file 
slidingWindowSize = 10 requests monitored
failureRateThreshold = if 50% fail → open circuit
waitDurationInOpenState = wait 10 seconds before retry
halfOpenCalls = allow 3 test calls

One theory is when if the threshold >50% then the OPEN circuit will execute it triggers fallbackMethod() , permittedNumberOfCallsInHalfOpenState is 3 , means Circuit breaker allows few requests to check if service recovered. (if success Circuit closes again, if failure Circuit opens again)

